<item>
            <title>[HBASE-535] REST servlet should allow content bodies to be gzipped, incoming or outgoing</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-535</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We could probably save a lot of network traffic by gzipping our requests and responses to REST when possible. A fair number of client libraries support this feature out of the box, and others could be fairly easily coded to work that way. Our content on requests and responses is probably very compressible, seeing as it is base64 encoded.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12391986">HBASE-535</key>
            <summary>REST servlet should allow content bodies to be gzipped, incoming or outgoing</summary>
